# Tool permission chat fallback

The owner sometimes **cannot see** Cursor's permission popup (often when nearing **usage limit**). **Chat approval still works.**

## Every time you need extra permissions

When a command needs `network`, `full_network`, `git_write`, `all`, or similar:

1. **In the same chat message**, say plainly what you need and why — e.g. *"Need network for Firebase deploy — if you don't see a popup, approve here in chat."*
2. **Do not rely on the popup alone** — the chat line is the backup when the UI is broken.
3. **Do not silently wait** on a permission prompt with no chat text.

## If blocked ~30 seconds

If a command is waiting on permission/sandbox and the owner has not responded within **~30 seconds**:

1. **Stop retrying silently.**
2. **Send a short chat message** restating the permission needed and what you're trying to do.
3. Prefer the **smallest** permission that works, or offer an alternate (e.g. owner runs one command locally).

## When popups work normally

Still include **one brief chat line** the first time you need a new permission type in the session — covers the usage-limit case without extra noise later.

## Do not

- Repeat the same permission request without explaining in chat.
- Assume silence means denial — nudge in chat after ~30s.
- Request `all` / disable sandbox unless actually required.
